26/05/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Army chief General Nikola Kolev said Wednesday (25 May) that the possible opening of US military bases in the country would happen in late 2006 or early 2007, at the earliest. 
He confirmed that the two sides are still negotiating, with an agreement expected by this fall.
In Bucharest meanwhile, the head of the Romanian Army's Strategic Planning Division, Brigadier General Valeriu Nicut, said Wednesday that US military bases would open in the southeast Dobrogea region within a year. 
(Sega - 26/05/05; Rompres - 25/05/05)
